pr_review_comment_body:
This will end up triggering when `window['name'] == None`.  Anyhow I'm not sure that this is an issue, more observation, so I'm happy with this to stay as it is.

To be honest I'm not why we are returning the transformed to i3bar it does not seem to be part of the protocol.

@ultrabug do you know anything about the transformed stuff?

This forces the result to be a numpy masked array. Could you do:

```
if i == 0:
    ...
elif isinstance(result, np.ma.MaskedArray):
    result = np.ma.row_stack((result, next_result))
else:
    result = np.row_stack((result, next_result))
```

This argument signature seems rigid.  It means if there is a parent, then you can't write `values='xyz'` because a keyword arg can't come before a `*arg`.  What do you think of using a signature like this instead?

    def add_profile(self, version=None, value=None, parents=())

Then expect `parents` to contain an iterable.
